{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E9J2aeGH9x54inw4dTVi64","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report for you.\n\n## Summary: Git Diff and Documentation Analysis\n\nBased on my analysis of the git diff and documentation, here's what has changed and what the docs currently describe:\n\n### Key Source Code Changes\n\nThe current git diff implements a **\"run title\" feature** that allows labeling workflow runs with a one-line summary. Here are the major changes:\n\n#### 1. **Protocol/API Changes** (api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto and api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go)\n- Added `title` field (string) to three protobuf messages:\n  - `RunWorkflowRequest` (field 6) - input for launching a run with a title\n  - `GetStatusResponse` (field 10) - output when checking run status\n  - `RunSummary` (field 7) - metadata in run list responses\n\n#### 2. **CLI Changes** (cmd/cloche/main.go)\n- Added `--title \"...\"` flag to the `cloche run` command\n- Usage string updated: `cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]`\n- Title is displayed in `cloche status` output (only if set)\n- Title appears in `cloche list` output (truncated to 40 chars, with ellipsis if longer)\n\n#### 3. **Daemon/Server Changes** (internal/adapters/grpc/server.go)\n- Reads title from `RunWorkflowRequest` and stores it in the Run domain object\n- Listens for `protocol.MsgRunTitle` messages from the agent (allows agent to auto-generate titles)\n- **Key logic**: If an explicit title is provided via `--title`, it takes precedence; otherwise the agent can set one via `MsgRunTitle` message\n- Includes title in both `GetStatus` and `ListRuns` responses\n\n#### 4. **Database/Persistence** (internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go)\n- Added `title` column to the `runs` table (TEXT, NOT NULL DEFAULT '')\n- Updated all SQL queries (INSERT, SELECT, UPDATE) to handle the title column\n- Migration adds the column to existing databases\n\n#### 5. **Domain Model** (internal/domain/run.go)\n- Added `Title string` field to the `Run` struct with comment: \"One-line summary of the work being done\"\n\n#### 6. **Status Protocol** (internal/protocol/status.go)\n- Added new message type `MsgRunTitle` (value: \"run_title\")\n- Added `StatusWriter.RunTitle(title string)` method to emit run titles\n\n#### 7. **Agent Auto-Title Generation** (internal/agent/runner.go)\n- New `extractTitle()` function that:\n  - Reads the per-run prompt file (`.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`) or falls back to `.cloche/prompt.txt`\n  - Extracts the first non-empty line (skipping markdown headers `#`, code fence markers, blanks)\n  - Truncates to 100 characters with ellipsis if needed\n  - Returns a one-line summary suitable as a run title\n- Runner calls `extractTitle()` early and reports it via `statusWriter.RunTitle()`\n\n#### 8. **Web UI** (internal/adapters/web/)\n- **handler.go**: Added `Title` field to `apiRun` struct (JSON API)\n- **run_detail.html**: Shows title at top of run details (only if set)\n- **runs.html**: \n  - Added \"Title\" column to runs table\n  - Updated colspan from 8 to 9 columns for empty state\n  - Truncates titles to 50 characters with ellipsis\n  - Escapes HTML in title output\n\n#### 9. **Tests** \nComprehensive new tests added in:\n- **server_test.go**: \n  - `TestServer_RunWorkflow_WithTitle` - explicit title is stored and returned\n  - `TestServer_RunWorkflow_AgentGeneratesTitle` - agent-generated title via MsgRunTitle\n  - `TestServer_RunWorkflow_ExplicitTitleNotOverriddenByAgent` - explicit title takes precedence\n  - `TestServer_ListRuns_IncludesTitle` - title appears in list responses\n- **store_test.go**:\n  - `TestRunTitle` - title persists through create/update/read\n  - `TestRunTitle_BackwardCompat` - empty title for pre-migration rows\n- **runner_test.go**:\n  - `TestRunner_ExtractsTitle` - prompt extraction works\n  - `TestRunner_TitleTruncation` - very long prompts truncate to 100 chars\n- **status_test.go**: `TestStatusWriter_RunTitle` - protocol message works\n\n### Current Documentation Status\n\nThe documentation files I reviewed don't yet mention the title feature:\n\n1. **docs/workflows.md** - No mention of title/summary (covers DSL syntax, step types, execution model)\n2. **docs/USAGE.md** - No mention of `--title` flag in the `cloche run` command documentation\n3. **docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md** - No mention of titles\n4. **docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md** - Focused on output mapping feature, not titles\n\nThe USAGE.md file currently shows:\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\nBut should be updated to:\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n### What the Feature Does\n\n**Purpose**: Provide human-readable labels for workflow runs instead of relying on numeric run IDs.\n\n**How it works**:\n1. User can provide explicit title via `cloche run --title \"Add dark mode toggle\"`\n2. If no explicit title, agent extracts one from the first line of the user's prompt\n3. Agent-generated titles can be overridden only if no explicit title was provided\n4. Titles are stored in the database, displayed in CLI status/list output, and shown in web UI\n5. Titles are truncated for display (40 chars in CLI list, 50 chars in web UI)\n\n**Key files affected**: \n- Protobuf definitions and generated code\n- CLI, daemon gRPC server, SQLite store\n- Agent runner with prompt extraction logic\n- Domain model\n- Web UI templates\n- Status protocol\n\nAll file paths are absolute and listed in `/workspace/` since this is the git repository root."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa37d984ed93f2ff2 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51142\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 24920</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"843502bc-3d5c-43fd-9244-ee919bbc5a7b","uuid":"3ef5d8ed-1100-4a6c-9857-8537a640b8ef","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Look at the current git diff (unstaged changes) to understand what was changed. Run `git diff` to see all modifications. Also look at the documentation files in docs/ directory - find all .md files there and read them. I need to understand what source code changes were made and what the docs currently say, so I can compare them.\n\nFocus on:\n1. The full git diff output\n2. All markdown files in docs/ directory\n3. Any references to \"title\" or \"summary\" in the codebase","agentId":"aa37d984ed93f2ff2","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report for you.\n\n## Summary: Git Diff and Documentation Analysis\n\nBased on my analysis of the git diff and documentation, here's what has changed and what the docs currently describe:\n\n### Key Source Code Changes\n\nThe current git diff implements a **\"run title\" feature** that allows labeling workflow runs with a one-line summary. Here are the major changes:\n\n#### 1. **Protocol/API Changes** (api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto and api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go)\n- Added `title` field (string) to three protobuf messages:\n  - `RunWorkflowRequest` (field 6) - input for launching a run with a title\n  - `GetStatusResponse` (field 10) - output when checking run status\n  - `RunSummary` (field 7) - metadata in run list responses\n\n#### 2. **CLI Changes** (cmd/cloche/main.go)\n- Added `--title \"...\"` flag to the `cloche run` command\n- Usage string updated: `cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]`\n- Title is displayed in `cloche status` output (only if set)\n- Title appears in `cloche list` output (truncated to 40 chars, with ellipsis if longer)\n\n#### 3. **Daemon/Server Changes** (internal/adapters/grpc/server.go)\n- Reads title from `RunWorkflowRequest` and stores it in the Run domain object\n- Listens for `protocol.MsgRunTitle` messages from the agent (allows agent to auto-generate titles)\n- **Key logic**: If an explicit title is provided via `--title`, it takes precedence; otherwise the agent can set one via `MsgRunTitle` message\n- Includes title in both `GetStatus` and `ListRuns` responses\n\n#### 4. **Database/Persistence** (internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go)\n- Added `title` column to the `runs` table (TEXT, NOT NULL DEFAULT '')\n- Updated all SQL queries (INSERT, SELECT, UPDATE) to handle the title column\n- Migration adds the column to existing databases\n\n#### 5. **Domain Model** (internal/domain/run.go)\n- Added `Title string` field to the `Run` struct with comment: \"One-line summary of the work being done\"\n\n#### 6. **Status Protocol** (internal/protocol/status.go)\n- Added new message type `MsgRunTitle` (value: \"run_title\")\n- Added `StatusWriter.RunTitle(title string)` method to emit run titles\n\n#### 7. **Agent Auto-Title Generation** (internal/agent/runner.go)\n- New `extractTitle()` function that:\n  - Reads the per-run prompt file (`.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`) or falls back to `.cloche/prompt.txt`\n  - Extracts the first non-empty line (skipping markdown headers `#`, code fence markers, blanks)\n  - Truncates to 100 characters with ellipsis if needed\n  - Returns a one-line summary suitable as a run title\n- Runner calls `extractTitle()` early and reports it via `statusWriter.RunTitle()`\n\n#### 8. **Web UI** (internal/adapters/web/)\n- **handler.go**: Added `Title` field to `apiRun` struct (JSON API)\n- **run_detail.html**: Shows title at top of run details (only if set)\n- **runs.html**: \n  - Added \"Title\" column to runs table\n  - Updated colspan from 8 to 9 columns for empty state\n  - Truncates titles to 50 characters with ellipsis\n  - Escapes HTML in title output\n\n#### 9. **Tests** \nComprehensive new tests added in:\n- **server_test.go**: \n  - `TestServer_RunWorkflow_WithTitle` - explicit title is stored and returned\n  - `TestServer_RunWorkflow_AgentGeneratesTitle` - agent-generated title via MsgRunTitle\n  - `TestServer_RunWorkflow_ExplicitTitleNotOverriddenByAgent` - explicit title takes precedence\n  - `TestServer_ListRuns_IncludesTitle` - title appears in list responses\n- **store_test.go**:\n  - `TestRunTitle` - title persists through create/update/read\n  - `TestRunTitle_BackwardCompat` - empty title for pre-migration rows\n- **runner_test.go**:\n  - `TestRunner_ExtractsTitle` - prompt extraction works\n  - `TestRunner_TitleTruncation` - very long prompts truncate to 100 chars\n- **status_test.go**: `TestStatusWriter_RunTitle` - protocol message works\n\n### Current Documentation Status\n\nThe documentation files I reviewed don't yet mention the title feature:\n\n1. **docs/workflows.md** - No mention of title/summary (covers DSL syntax, step types, execution model)\n2. **docs/USAGE.md** - No mention of `--title` flag in the `cloche run` command documentation\n3. **docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md** - No mention of titles\n4. **docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md** - Focused on output mapping feature, not titles\n\nThe USAGE.md file currently shows:\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\nBut should be updated to:\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n### What the Feature Does\n\n**Purpose**: Provide human-readable labels for workflow runs instead of relying on numeric run IDs.\n\n**How it works**:\n1. User can provide explicit title via `cloche run --title \"Add dark mode toggle\"`\n2. If no explicit title, agent extracts one from the first line of the user's prompt\n3. Agent-generated titles can be overridden only if no explicit title was provided\n4. Titles are stored in the database, displayed in CLI status/list output, and shown in web UI\n5. Titles are truncated for display (40 chars in CLI list, 50 chars in web UI)\n\n**Key files affected**: \n- Protobuf definitions and generated code\n- CLI, daemon gRPC server, SQLite store\n- Agent runner with prompt extraction logic\n- Domain model\n- Web UI templates\n- Status protocol\n\nAll file paths are absolute and listed in `/workspace/` since this is the git repository root."}],"totalDurationMs":24920,"totalTokens":51142,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4689,"cache_read_input_tokens":44861,"output_tokens":1585,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4689},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
